<br>
Lets face it, no one's getting really rich off this, but when I see folks dropping prices to just above cost and essentially making pennies all its doing is setting a really bad expectation for our customers.  I think the worst was when I saw SOW potions drop below the 80p barrier with someone spamming 75p 10 dosers in PoK.  Personally, I don't think the carpel tunnel syndrome is worth the small profit from SOW potions, but with some of the higher margin potions, folks are really killing the market.  <br>
<br>
Potions like gate potions and benefit potions should be higher since you can use 9 of the 10 doses and still sell the damn thing back to merchants for 1k plat and up!  Recently, I've seen folks dumping 5 dose and 10 dose gate potions for 1500 and 3000 respectively.  Now if you assume that you are successful 90% of the time (so 1 fizzle out of 10) and you brew a 10 dose that you resell for 3k, your effective cost for that 10 doser is gonna be around 2800, which gives you a proft of 200p.  In the event that you fizzle twice for that 10 doser, you end up losing money.  When you consider the fact that the Xev community has shown that they will pay 375-400p per dose for gate potions, 3k for a 10 doser is way too low.  Same goes for sow potions (for all you young alchemists).  The price has slowly dropped from 110p per 10 dose to the standard price of 80p now.  <br>
<br>
I'd like to hear what other folks think, since none of us spent the 20-30k to become master and GM alchemists just so we can brew potions for our friends at cost and never make any money off it.<br>
